<DOC><DOCNO> AP880910-0014 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-10-88 0121EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r w BC-TextileBill-Glance     09-10 0117</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Textile Bill-Glance,120</SECOND><HEAD>With PM-Textile Bill Bjt</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Here at a glance are provisions of the textiletrade legislation approved Friday by the Senate:   TEXTILE AND APPAREL IMPORTS   Freezes overall textile and apparel imports this year at 1987levels and limits future growth to one percent annually.   NONRUBBER FOOTWEAR IMPORTS   Freezes overall imports of nonrubber footwear at 1987 levelswith no provision for increases in the future.   AGRICULTURAL PROVISION   Provides for preferred trade treatment for countries thatincrease their purchases of U.S. agricultural goods.   AUCTIONED QUOTAS   Requires the government to auction off import quotas amongAmerican importing companies.   COMPENSATION   Authorizes the president to negotiate reduced tariffs tocompensate countries hurt by tightened import restraints.</TEXT></DOC>